06/08/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Supreme Military Council wrapped up its annual session on Thursday (5 August). Its members decided that Land Forces Commander General Aytac Yalman and Gendarme Forces Commander General Mehmet Sener Eruygur would retire as of 1 September. Yalman would be replaced by Deputy Chief of Staff General Yasar Buyukanit and Eruygur by General Fevzi Turkeri. The Council also decided to dismiss 12 army officers for violating military discipline guidelines. (NTV, Anadolu Agency - 05/08/04)
